        "subject": "LU-6391 llite: mount option for client not to stop pinging",
        "message": "LU-6391 llite: mount option for client not to stop pinging\n\nWhen Lustre servers enable 'suppress_pings', all clients will stop\npinging. However, some clients may not have external mechanism\nto notify Lustre servers for node death and therefore need to\npreserve the Lustre ping.\n\nThis patch provides an mount option 'always_ping' so that the\nclient will not stop pinging even server enabled 'suppress_pings'.\n\nSigned-off-by: Wally Wang <wang@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I8adaf42c9a7703251a34f350a42afc52f3301664\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
